<paragraph blockId="30.[151,422,1602,1628]" box="[151,422,1602,1628]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,422,1602,1628]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[151,422,1602,1628]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,422,1602,1628]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,231,1602,1628]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[237,422,1602,1628]" pageId="30" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number box="[363,422,1602,1628]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1674,2036]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The plate 
<number box="[270,314,1674,1700]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="666.0">666</number>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[355,541,1674,1700]" pageId="30" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault (
<number box="[472,534,1674,1700]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1764.0">1764</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
shows his 
<taxonomicName box="[674,750,1675,1700]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[674,750,1675,1700]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or “Vipere”, clearly an “asp viper”, a common species in western Europe, currently known as 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[604,977,1712,1738]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aspis">
<emphasis box="[604,757,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera aspis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[775,968,1712,1738]" pageId="30" pageNumber="42" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decima, reformata. Tomus I. Holmiae, Laurentii Salvii, [i - iv] + 1 - 824." type="book chapter" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[905,968,1712,1738]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(family 
<taxonomicName authority="Oppel, 1811" authorityName="Oppel" authorityYear="1811" box="[1084,1368,1712,1738]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
<emphasis box="[1084,1209,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">VIPERIDAE</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Oppel" box="[1218,1368,1712,1738]" pageId="30" pageNumber="43" refString="Oppel, M. (1811 a) Ordre II. Reptiles a ecailles. Section 2. Ophidiens. Annales du Museum d'Histoire naturelle, &quot; 1810 &quot;, 16, 254 - 295 + 376 - 393." type="journal article" year="1811" yearSuffix="a">
Oppel, 
<number box="[1308,1368,1712,1738]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1811.0">1811</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1369,1384,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">a</emphasis>
). In agreement with this figure, we hereby designate 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[742,1105,1749,1775]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aspis">
<emphasis box="[742,911,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Coluber aspis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[919,1105,1749,1775]" pageId="30" pageNumber="42" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decima, reformata. Tomus I. Holmiae, Laurentii Salvii, [i - iv] + 1 - 824." type="book chapter" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[1045,1105,1749,1775]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as nucleospecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1356,1434,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[151,339,1786,1812]" pageId="30" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number box="[273,339,1786,1812]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[353,387,1786,1812]" name="American Samoa" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">As</collectingCountry>
discussed below, the latter generic nomen is both a senior hadromonym and senior doxisonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[320,581,1824,1850]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[320,395,1824,1849]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[405,581,1824,1850]" pageId="30" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[519,581,1824,1850]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1674,2036]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Laurenti’s (
<number box="[333,397,1861,1887]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1768.0">1768</number>
: 
<number box="[408,439,1861,1887]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="99.0">99</number>
) genus 
<taxonomicName box="[531,606,1861,1886]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[531,606,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described with ten prenucleospecies. The nomina of two of them, 
<taxonomicName authority="Francisci Redi" authorityName="Francisci Redi" box="[151,411,1899,1924]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,411,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera Francisci Redi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mosis Charas" authorityName="Mosis Charas" box="[469,719,1899,1924]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[469,719,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera Mosis Charas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are trinomina, but, as discussed above, they can be “saved” through the use of Article 11.9. 
<number box="[519,533,1936,1962]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="5.0">5</number>
, and must now be spelt 
<taxonomicName box="[815,1048,1936,1961]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="francisciredi">
<emphasis box="[815,1048,1936,1961]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera francisciredi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1106,1338,1936,1961]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mosischaras">
<emphasis box="[1106,1338,1936,1961]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera mosischaras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1674,2036]" lastBlockId="31.[151,1437,152,1186]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<bibRefCitation author="Gmelin" box="[198,367,1973,1999]" pageId="30" pageNumber="40" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1789) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locus. Editio decima tertia, aucta, reformata. Tomus 1, pars 3. Lugduni, Delamolliere, 1033 - 1516." type="journal article" year="1789">
Gmelin (
<number box="[303,367,1973,1999]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1789.0">1789</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[378,438,1973,1999]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1091.0">1091</number>
) created the nomen 
<taxonomicName box="[677,827,1973,1998]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="redi">
<emphasis box="[677,827,1973,1998]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Coluber redi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He mentioned the nomen 
<taxonomicName authority="Francisci Redi" authorityName="Francisci Redi" box="[1146,1406,1973,1998]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1146,1406,1973,1998]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera Francisci Redi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its synonymy, so his nomen must be considered an autoneonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[966,1398,2010,2036]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="francisciredi">
<emphasis box="[966,1208,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Vipera francisciredi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[1217,1398,2010,2036]" pageId="30" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[1335,1398,2010,2036]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as acknowledged by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mertens" box="[369,764,152,178]" pageId="31" pageNumber="43" refString="Mertens, R. &amp; Wermuth, H. (1960) Die Amphibien und Reptilien Europas. Dritte Liste, nach dem Stand vom 1. Januar 1960. Frankfurt am Main, Waldemar Kramer, i - xi, 1 - 264." type="journal article" year="1960">
Mertens &amp; Wermuth (
<number box="[632,697,152,178]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1960.0">1960</number>
: 
<number box="[709,755,152,178]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="195.0">195</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="McDiarmid" box="[823,1113,152,178]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="McDiarmid, R. W., Campbell, J. A. &amp; Toure, T. A. (1999) Snake species of the world. A taxonomic and geographic reference. Volume 1. Wahington, The Herpetologists's League, i - xi + 1 - 511." type="book chapter" year="1999">
McDiarmid 
<emphasis box="[970,1031,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1048,1113,152,178]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[1125,1174,152,178]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="393.0">393</number>
). The nomen 
<taxonomicName authority="Gmelin, 1789" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1789" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="redi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Coluber redi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gmelin" box="[208,377,189,215]" pageId="31" pageNumber="40" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1789) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locus. Editio decima tertia, aucta, reformata. Tomus 1, pars 3. Lugduni, Delamolliere, 1033 - 1516." type="journal article" year="1789">
Gmelin, 
<number box="[316,377,189,215]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1789.0">1789</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is an invalid junior isonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[760,1199,189,215]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="francisciredi">
<emphasis box="[760,1006,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera francisciredi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[1014,1199,189,215]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[1135,1199,189,215]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, therefore a nomen distinct from the latter. It was not part of the prenucleospecies of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[1079,1350,226,252]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1079,1157,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[1168,1350,226,252]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[1287,1350,226,252]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and is therefore not eligible for nucleospecies designation for the latter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,152,1186]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<collectingCountry box="[198,231,301,327]" name="American Samoa" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">As</collectingCountry>
a consequence, Fitzinger’s (
<number box="[577,641,301,327]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1843.0">1843</number>
: 
<number box="[655,686,301,327]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="28.0">28</number>
) designation of this nominal species (as “ 
<emphasis box="[1196,1314,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vip. Redii</emphasis>
Latr.”) as nucleospecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[364,443,338,363]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[364,443,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is invalid. It is therefore in error that 
<bibRefCitation author="Stejneger" box="[928,1197,338,364]" pageId="31" pageNumber="45" refString="Stejneger, L. (1936) Types of the amphibian and reptilian genera proposed by Laurenti in 1768. Copeia, 1936 (3), 133 - 141." type="journal article" year="1936">
Stejneger (
<number box="[1061,1128,338,364]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1936.0">1936</number>
: 
<number box="[1141,1188,338,364]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="140.0">140</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
wrote: “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">This being Laurenti’s</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[276,515,376,402]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="francisci" subSpecies="redi">Vipera francisci redi</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[523,676,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">which equals</emphasis>
[sic] 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" box="[743,1022,376,402]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aspis">
Coluber aspis 
<emphasis box="[912,1022,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Linnaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the latter becomes the genotype of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,236,413,439]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Vipera</taxonomicName>
”. This statement is twice wrong because neither 
<taxonomicName box="[810,960,413,438]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="redi">
<emphasis box="[810,960,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Coluber redi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor 
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1179,413,438]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aspis">
<emphasis box="[1015,1179,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Coluber aspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were members of the prenucleospecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[392,654,450,476]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[392,467,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[477,654,450,476]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[592,654,450,476]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, some subsequent authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Mertens" box="[1099,1387,450,476]" pageId="31" pageNumber="43" refString="Mertens, R. &amp; Muller, L. (1940) Die Amphibien und Reptilien Europas. (Zweite Liste, nach dem Stand vom 1. Januar 1940). Abhandlungen herausgegeben von der senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 451, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1940">
Mertens &amp; Müller 
<number box="[1324,1387,450,476]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1940.0">1940</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[1398,1431,450,476]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="54.0">54</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="McDiarmid" box="[151,455,488,514]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="McDiarmid, R. W., Campbell, J. A. &amp; Toure, T. A. (1999) Snake species of the world. A taxonomic and geographic reference. Volume 1. Wahington, The Herpetologists's League, i - xi + 1 - 511." type="book chapter" year="1999">
McDiarmid 
<emphasis box="[309,376,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[386,455,488,514]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[469,519,488,514]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="389.0">389</number>
) followed this error and considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Gmelin, 1789" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1789" box="[997,1351,488,514]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="redi">
<emphasis box="[997,1164,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Coluber redi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gmelin" box="[1173,1351,488,514]" pageId="31" pageNumber="40" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1789) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locus. Editio decima tertia, aucta, reformata. Tomus 1, pars 3. Lugduni, Delamolliere, 1033 - 1516." type="journal article" year="1789">
Gmelin, 
<number box="[1287,1351,488,514]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1789.0">1789</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as the nucleospecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[361,631,525,551]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[361,438,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[449,631,525,551]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[567,631,525,551]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Mertens &amp; Wermuth’s (
<number box="[931,997,525,551]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1960.0">1960</number>
: 
<number box="[1009,1056,525,551]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="194.0">194</number>
) subsequent mention of 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="francisci" subSpecies="redi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera francisci redi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as “ 
<emphasis box="[357,521,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">species typica</emphasis>
” of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[571,828,562,588]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[571,646,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[655,828,562,588]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[769,828,562,588]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was the first to cite this biological species under the nomen used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[346,543,600,626]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti (
<number box="[467,534,600,626]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. This statement was repeated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruno" box="[952,1169,600,626]" pageId="31" pageNumber="37" refString="Bruno, S. (1985) Le vipere d'Italia e d'Europa. Bologna, Edagricole, i - viii + 1 - 272, pl. 1 - 12." type="book chapter" year="1985">
Bruno (
<number box="[1046,1112,600,626]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1985.0">1985</number>
: 
<number box="[1125,1160,600,626]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="40.0">40</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Although based on a wrong interpretation, this would indeed be the valid designation of a nucleospecies for this genus if it was not predated by another designation. 
<collectingCountry box="[561,595,674,700]" name="American Samoa" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">As</collectingCountry>
a matter of fact, and even if they ignored it later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mertens" pageId="31" pageNumber="43" refString="Mertens, R. &amp; Muller, L. (1928) Liste der Amphibien und Reptilien Europas. Abhandlungen herausgegeben von der senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 41, 1 - 62." type="journal article" year="1928">
Mertens &amp; Müller (
<number box="[160,226,712,738]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1928.0">1928</number>
: 
<number box="[239,270,712,738]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="51.0">51</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
had previously designated 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[616,983,712,738]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="illyrica">
<emphasis box="[616,794,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera illyrica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[802,983,712,738]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[922,983,712,738]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as nucleospecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1236,1315,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[151,214,749,775]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This nominal species was part of the prenucleospecies of the genus, so this designation, which is the first 
<emphasis box="[205,267,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Code</emphasis>
-compliant one to have been published, is valid. The nomen 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1142,786,811]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="illyrica">
<emphasis box="[973,1142,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera illyrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior doxisonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[151,574,824,850]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ammodytes">
<emphasis box="[151,368,824,849]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera ammodytes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[383,566,824,850]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decima, reformata. Tomus I. Holmiae, Laurentii Salvii, [i - iv] + 1 - 824." type="book chapter" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[506,566,824,850]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Mertens" box="[637,949,824,850]" pageId="31" pageNumber="43" refString="Mertens, R. &amp; Wermuth, H. (1960) Die Amphibien und Reptilien Europas. Dritte Liste, nach dem Stand vom 1. Januar 1960. Frankfurt am Main, Waldemar Kramer, i - xi, 1 - 264." type="journal article" year="1960">
Mertens &amp; Wermuth 
<number box="[886,949,824,850]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1960.0">1960</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[960,1008,824,850]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="194.0">194</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,152,1186]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[198,462,861,887]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[198,274,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[286,462,861,887]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[403,462,861,887]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore an invalid junior doxisonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[1002,1268,861,887]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1002,1077,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[1089,1268,861,887]" pageId="31" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number box="[1206,1268,861,887]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[1282,1314,861,887]" name="American Samoa" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">As</collectingCountry>
both taxa 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[151,509,898,924]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aspis">
<emphasis box="[151,317,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Coluber aspis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[326,509,898,924]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decima, reformata. Tomus I. Holmiae, Laurentii Salvii, [i - iv] + 1 - 824." type="book chapter" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[450,509,898,924]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[569,926,898,924]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="illyrica">
<emphasis box="[569,742,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera illyrica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[750,926,898,924]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[867,926,898,924]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are currently referred by all authors to the same genus 
<taxonomicName box="[298,375,936,961]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[298,375,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and even to the same “group” (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Obst" box="[818,943,936,962]" pageId="31" pageNumber="43" refString="Obst, F. J. (1983) Zur Kenntnis der Schlangengattung Vipera (Reptilia, Serpentes, Viperidae). Zoologische Abhandlungen aus dem Staatliche Museum fur Tierkunde in Dresden, 38 (13), 229 - 235." type="journal article" year="1983">
Obst 
<number box="[882,943,936,962]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) or subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1112,1189,936,961]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1112,1189,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Mallow" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Mallow, D., Ludwig, D. &amp; Nilson, G. (2003) True vipers. Natural history and toxinology of Old World vipers. Malabar, Florida, Krieger, i - xiv + 1 - 359." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Mallow 
<emphasis box="[1368,1429,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[151,220,973,999]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the shift of authorship and date of the nomen of this genus has no disturbing nomenclatural consequences and must be implemented, as already suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Welter-Schultes" box="[973,1432,1010,1036]" pageId="31" pageNumber="46" refString="Welter-Schultes, F. W. &amp; Klug, R. (2009) Nomenclatural consequences resulting from the rediscovery of Les figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medicine, a rare work published by Garsault in 1764, in the zoological literature. Bulletin of zoological Nomenclature, 66 (3), 225 - 241." type="journal article" year="2009">
Welter-Schultes &amp; Klug (
<number box="[1291,1359,1010,1036]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2009.0">2009</number>
: 
<number box="[1372,1423,1010,1036]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="238.0">238</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Therefore no change is required in the binomina of the 
<number box="[801,830,1048,1074]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="27.0">27</number>
species currently recognized in this genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Mallow" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Mallow, D., Ludwig, D. &amp; Nilson, G. (2003) True vipers. Natural history and toxinology of Old World vipers. Malabar, Florida, Krieger, i - xiv + 1 - 359." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Mallow 
<emphasis box="[151,203,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[218,278,1085,1111]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and their subspecies. The only change needed in their nominal-complexes is the inclusion of the author’s 
<taxonomicName box="[257,322,1122,1148]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="name">name</taxonomicName>
and date between parentheses, to point to the transfer from 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[1051,1316,1122,1148]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1051,1128,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenti" box="[1139,1316,1122,1148]" pageId="31" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number box="[1256,1316,1122,1148]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1356,1433,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Vipera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[151,327,1160,1186]" pageId="31" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number box="[265,327,1160,1186]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
